<div>
  <div data-controls>
    <button class="btn btn-info tutorial-next"><%- gettext("Ok got it, Next") %> <i class="icon-caret-right"></i></button>
    <button class="btn btn-link-secondary tutorial-end" href="#"><%- gettext("Skip the rest of this tutorial") %></a>
  </div>
  <div data-step="welcome">
    <p class="loud">
      <%- gettext("Welcome to Appmaker. We'll start with a short tour.") %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="bricks">
    <p>
      <%- gettext("These are called <strong>bricks</strong>. A brick is a piece of code that allows a user to cause an interaction. For example, the <em>button</em> brick places a button on the page that a user can click. You can also make a brick automatically do something based on other interactions. For example, the <em>fireworks</em> brick can be set to react to the clicking of a button or can be set to go off at regular intervals. You can add bricks to your app by clicking on them. To learn more about each brick, hover over the <strong>?</strong> icon to the right of each brick.") %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="customize">
    <p>
      <%- gettext("Once you choose your bricks you can customize them by changing color, size, or other attributes.") %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="project-settings">
    <p>
      <%- gettext("Give your app a fancy name, description, and tags.") %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="pages">
    <p>
      <%- gettext("You can add pages to your app here.") %>
      <img src="" alt="">
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="channels">
    <p>
      <%- gettext("Once you add bricks to your app you will notice these lines.") %>
      <img src="" alt="">
      <%- gettext("They are called channels and they connect inputs (like this button) to outputs (like these waving hands).") %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="colors">
    <p>
      <%- gettext("If you have more than one input and output, click on the connector to switch colors.") %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div data-step="end">
    <p class="loud">
      <%- gettext("That's it! Now go ahead and start building an app. Happy making!") %>
    </p>
    <button class="btn btn-info tutorial-end"><%- gettext("Done") %></button>
  </div>
</div>
